'''Mathias Katamba''' is a [[Uganda]]n [[economist]], [[business executive]], [[banker]] and [[entrepreneur]]. He is the [[Managing Director]] and [[Chief Executive Officer]] of [[DFCU Bank]], the second-largest commercial bank in Uganda, effective January 2019.<ref name="1R">{{cite web|date=31 October 2018 |url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/News/National/Dfcu-appoints-Katamba-announces-Kisaame-exit/688334-4830474-c21sm1/index.html |
title=Dfcu appoints Katamba, announces Kisaame exit |
access-date=31 October 2018 |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] | first=Dorothy |last=Nakaweesi |location=Kampala}}</ref>

Before that, he was the managing director and CEO of [[Housing Finance Bank]], a [[commercial bank]], co-owned by the Ugandan government and the [[National Social Security Fund (Uganda)]], a semi-autonomous retirement pension organisation for non-government employees in Uganda.<ref name="1R"/><ref name="2R">{{cite web|title=Katamba quits Housing Finance, linked to dfcu | url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/Business/Finance/Katamba-quits-Housing-Finance-dfcu-/688608-4826600-klc7c3/index.html |date=29 October 2018 |access-date=31 October 2018 |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |first=Dorothy |last=Nakaweesi |location=Kampala}}</ref>

==Background==
He was born in [[Central Region, Uganda|Central Uganda]].

==Education==
Katamba had his early education in Uganda. He then entered the [[University of Greenwich]], in England, graduating with the degree of [[Economics|Bachelor of Arts in Economics]]. His degree of [[Financial Management|Master of Science in Financial Management]] was obtained from the [[University of East London]], also in the [[UK]]. He also holds the postgraduate [[Public relations|Diploma in Public Relations]], awarded by the [[Chartered Institute of Public Relations]] (CIPR), another UK institution. Over the years, he has attended advanced leadership courses from several institutions, including [[Harvard Kennedy School]] and [[Wharton Business School]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Progression Capital Africa: Mathias Katamba|
url=http://www.progressioncapitalafrica.com/mathias.html|accessdate=24 April 2014| publisher=Progression Capital Africa}}</ref>

==Work experience==
Even while still in school, Katamba exhibited entrepreneurial skill, by starting a business during the break between middle and high school.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/8/13/689257|title=My First Job: Mathias Katamba|publisher=[[New Vision]]|date=26 July 2009|first=Archive|last=Newvision|
accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

For the past 10 to 15 years, he has been intimately associated with [[Uganda]]'s banking industry. He is credited with:

*The transformation of [[Pride Microfinance Limited]] from a [[Non-Government Organization]] (NGO), into a [[Banking in Uganda|Tier III]] Deposit-taking microfinance financial institution (MFI).
* The transformation of '''Uganda Finance Trust Limited''', from a [[Banking in Uganda|Tier III]], Deposit-Taking MFI into  a [[Banking in Uganda|Tier 1]] commercial bank, [[Finance Trust Bank]].<ref>{{cite web|title=When Finance Trust Made The Turn of Its Life|url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/Business/Prosper/-/688616/943460/-/iyj35uz/-/index.html|first=Fredrick|last=Masiga|date=22 June 2010|
accessdate=24 April 2014|publisher=[[Daily Monitor]]}}</ref>

In 2011, following 5 years at the helm of [[Uganda Finance Trust Limited]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Katamba Says Adieus to Banking|date=20 September 2011| 
url=http://www.archives.in2eastafrica.net/katamba-says-adieus-to-banking/|
first=Reporter|last=In2EastAfrica|accessdate=24 April 2014|publisher=[[Daily Monitor]] via In2EastAfrica.net}}</ref> he took a beak from commercial banking until he was appointed to is present position in April 2014. Prior to his present position, he was Managing Partner and co-founder of ''Progression Capital Africa (PCA)'', a US$40 million private equity fund based in [[Mauritius]]. Before joining Finance Trust Bank, he worked at some national and regional, notable financial institutions; including  [[Orient Bank]], [[PostBank Uganda|Postbank]] and [[Absa Group Limited]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mathias Katamba Appointed New Housing Finance Bank Managing Director | url=http://www.sbreview.net/index.php/terms-of-use-and-privacy-policy/smes/components/content-component/article-categories/793-mathias-katamba-appointed-new-housing-finance-bank-managing-director| first=Editor|last=By|date=24 March 2014|accessdate=24 April 2014|publisher=Summit Business Review}}</ref>

